- $K_M$ is the [substrate] at which enzyme velocity is 50% maximal
-$K_M$ is an “apparent” dissociation constant (for Briggs-Haldane)
- Small $K_M$ means tight binding; high $K_M$ means weak binding
- Useful to compare $K_M$ for different substrates for one enzyme
- Useful to compare $K_M$ for a common substrate used by several enzymes
