*Linearized plots of steady-state kinetics data*
Lineweaver-Burk plot: $1/v_0$ vs. $1/ [S]$
The advantage of this plot is that the experimental points are better spread, so points at low $[S]$ are not emphasized disproportionately, as they are in Lineweaver-Burke plots.

